    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-03-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="104"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                <head>104. Memorandum From the <gloss type="from">Joint Chiefs of Staff</gloss> to
                    the Secretary of Defense (<persName corresp="#p_WCE1" type="to"
                        >Wilson</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d104fn1">Source:
                            <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> Library, Sp. Asst. for
                        Nat. Sec. Affairs Records. Top Secret. <persName corresp="#p_GG1">Gordon
                            Gray</persName> sent a copy of this memorandum to Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> on April 2. (Department of State,
                        Central Files, 780.5/4–256) Secretary of Defense <persName corresp="#p_WCE1"
                            >Wilson</persName> forwarded a copy of the memorandum to <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Executive Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_LJSJ1">Lay</persName> on April 5 (see <ref target="#d109"
                            >Document 109</ref>), who in turn transmitted both memoranda to the
                            <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>on April 9.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-03-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1956</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>U.S. Adherence to the Baghdad Pact</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>During the past year, the Joint Chiefs of Staff have on several occasions
                        expressed views to point out the military advantages of early United States
                        adherence to the Baghdad Pact, while recognizing the inherent implications
                        with regard to increased military and economic aid.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The Joint Chiefs of Staff realize that United States adherence to the
                        Baghdad Pact is but one of several actions being studied which may involve
                        the United States in the Middle East. However, the formation of the Baghdad
                        Pact organization, and particularly its military planning, is advancing
                        rapidly. In the light of this progress and of the critical situation in the
                        Middle East, the Joint Chiefs of Staff, from a military point of view,
                        recommend that the United States adhere to the Baghdad Pact without delay,
                        and that the Secretary of State be so advised.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="italic">For the Joint Chiefs of Staff:</hi>
                    <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RAAW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Arthur Radford</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <note n="2" xml:id="d104fn2">Printed from a copy that bears this typed
                            signature.</note>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chairman</hi>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Joint Chiefs of Staff</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
